00:31:18.492 --> 00:31:22.152
we have here three models. They were selected based on mRNA expression.

512
00:31:22.212 --> 00:31:25.752
We have a high LYS6E mRNA expression

513
00:31:26.232 --> 00:31:29.692
and folate alpha and kathorin-6 are expressed at various

514
00:31:30.212 --> 00:31:34.172
degrees of mRNA expression. And what we see is

515
00:31:34.272 --> 00:31:38.112
that with M7437, in the upper left, we have

516
00:31:38.152 --> 00:31:41.672
superior activity compared to both competitors.

517
00:31:42.192 --> 00:31:46.092
In the second model, next to the right, we have superior activity to

518
00:31:46.112 --> 00:31:49.952
Ralu-DXd and Rina-S and M7437

519
00:31:50.012 --> 00:31:53.892
are comparably efficacious. And in the lower left, we see

520
00:31:53.932 --> 00:31:56.212
high efficacy for all three molecules.

521
00:31:57.832 --> 00:32:01.732
And on the right-hand side, you see a gastric cancer PDX

522
00:32:01.772 --> 00:32:05.032
model, which was derived from a patient receiving

523
00:32:05.092 --> 00:32:09.012
Enhertu and who progressed in the first cycle on

524
00:32:09.212 --> 00:32:13.172
Enhertu. And here we see promising efficacy

525
00:32:13.312 --> 00:32:17.262
in this model with primary resistance to Enhertu or

526
00:32:17.592 --> 00:32:18.212
T-DXd.

527
00:32:21.932 --> 00:32:25.772
The preclinical safety was evaluated in a GLP

528
00:32:25.872 --> 00:32:29.552
repeated toxicity study, using cynomolgus

529
00:32:29.612 --> 00:32:32.932
monkeys as pharmacologically relevant species.

530
00:32:33.692 --> 00:32:36.572
And here it was very well tolerated.

531
00:32:37.092 --> 00:32:40.281
And we saw toxicities mainly

532
00:32:40.292 --> 00:32:43.732
characterized by effects on the hematological

533
00:32:44.092 --> 00:32:47.512
system. Lymphocytes, neutrophils, and reticulocytes were

534
00:32:47.572 --> 00:32:51.112
affected, and this was also in line with histopathological

535
00:32:51.232 --> 00:32:53.772
findings in lymphoid organs and the bone marrow.

536
00:32:55.732 --> 00:32:59.372
We investigated the PK and saw that we have

537
00:32:59.452 --> 00:33:03.232
a favorable profile regarding the PK and

538
00:33:03.512 --> 00:33:07.412
a very high stability of the ADC by analyzing both

539
00:33:07.452 --> 00:33:11.012
total antibody and antibody conjugated to the payload.

540
00:33:11.412 --> 00:33:15.032
We saw superimposed curves indicating a very high

541
00:33:15.112 --> 00:33:18.472
stability, which may also be attributed to the

542
00:33:18.532 --> 00:33:22.252
site-specific TGA's conjugation because it is not prone to

543
00:33:22.392 --> 00:33:25.312
retro-Michael, which, for example, is the case for

544
00:33:25.712 --> 00:33:29.632
maleimide conjugated ADCs using cysteine conjugation.

545
00:33:30.652 --> 00:33:34.472
On the right-hand side, you can see in vitro viability assays

546
00:33:34.532 --> 00:33:38.072
using human PBMCs. We looked at different

547
00:33:38.132 --> 00:33:42.112
subtypes, and we identified proliferating NK

548
00:33:42.172 --> 00:33:45.592
cells, that they were sensitive to M7437

549
00:33:45.652 --> 00:33:49.441
treatment, but we didn't see effects on resting NK cells, and

550
00:33:49.472 --> 00:33:52.532
the same was true for B and T cells,

551
00:33:53.152 --> 00:33:55.492
independent of their proliferative state.

552
00:33:57.392 --> 00:34:01.132
So in summary, M7437 is a novel, highly

553
00:34:01.212 --> 00:34:04.832
stable anti-LY6E ADC with a TOP1 inhibitor

554
00:34:04.842 --> 00:34:08.013
payload ekstatine, which was conjugated

555
00:34:08.572 --> 00:34:11.993
with transglutaminase to a DAR of four.

556
00:34:12.732 --> 00:34:16.372
We have high in vitro potency, including a potent bystander

557
00:34:16.432 --> 00:34:19.953
effect, indicating the potential to be effective in

558
00:34:20.712 --> 00:34:22.892
tumors with heterogeneous target expression.

559
00:34:23.272 --> 00:34:27.192
And this was substantiated in our PDX models, where

560
00:34:27.232 --> 00:34:31.072
we saw very high anti-tumor activity in models with a

561
00:34:31.092 --> 00:34:34.212
broad range of expression and a number of different

562
00:34:34.292 --> 00:34:38.112
indications. In addition, we saw superior activity compared to

563
00:34:38.152 --> 00:34:42.053
competitors, and together with an acceptable safety profile

564
00:34:42.112 --> 00:34:45.832
and favorable PK properties, the preclinical data

565
00:34:45.953 --> 00:34:49.592
package supports the further development of M7437.

566
00:34:50.042 --> 00:34:53.872
And recently we have started a phase one with an escalation phase and

567
00:34:53.932 --> 00:34:55.033
an expansion phase,

568
00:34:56.212 --> 00:34:59.592
where we look at safety tolerability, PK, and

569
00:34:59.832 --> 00:35:02.952
preliminary signs of activity in a range of tumor

570
00:35:02.992 --> 00:35:06.612
indications known to have high LYS6E expression.

571
00:35:08.012 --> 00:35:10.492
And with that, I would like to thank you for your attention.

572
00:35:16.232 --> 00:35:19.112
Well, we'll do online first. We have one question from online.

573
00:35:19.122 --> 00:35:21.372
"Congrats to you. Nice talk.

