00:38:05.402 --> 00:38:09.022
Toral Biotherapeutics, as well as 1200 Pharma.

626
00:38:14.602 --> 00:38:18.582
Thank you to ASOR and the chairs of the committee for selecting our abstract

627
00:38:18.642 --> 00:38:22.422
for presentation. Today, I'm going to talk about the preclinical evaluation of

628
00:38:22.462 --> 00:38:26.142
target-mediated clearance and alternative payloads in cadherin 17-directed

629
00:38:26.162 --> 00:38:27.342
antibody drug conjugates.

630
00:38:28.282 --> 00:38:29.022
My disclosures.

631
00:38:29.842 --> 00:38:31.322
So, some background on the target.

632
00:38:31.422 --> 00:38:35.062
Cadherin 17 is a single-pass transmembrane protein involved in

633
00:38:35.122 --> 00:38:38.482
calcium-dependent transport and maintenance of gastrointestinal

634
00:38:38.582 --> 00:38:42.102
architecture. However, in cancer, according to these

635
00:38:42.142 --> 00:38:45.962
TCGA data, mRNA expression of cadherin 17 is

636
00:38:46.022 --> 00:38:49.902
highly expressed in colorectal cancers, pancreas and stomach cancers, so highly

637
00:38:49.922 --> 00:38:53.842
expressed in gastrointestinal cancers, and largely absent from the majority

638
00:38:53.882 --> 00:38:57.742
of normal tissues throughout the body according to these GTEx data, aside

639
00:38:57.782 --> 00:39:01.222
from significant expression in normal colon and normal small

640
00:39:01.242 --> 00:39:05.232
intestine. And these data have created a lot of excitement around this target,

641
00:39:06.182 --> 00:39:09.462
and it's now considered one of the most exciting, or at least it's considered one

642
00:39:09.482 --> 00:39:13.342
of the most exciting emerging targets for antibody-based

643
00:39:13.362 --> 00:39:17.062
therapies. There's multiple antibody drug conjugates, CAR Ts,

644
00:39:17.182 --> 00:39:21.102
bispecific antibodies, bispecific ADCs

645
00:39:21.322 --> 00:39:25.102
in early-stage clinical development, many more in preclinical, and many more in

646
00:39:25.122 --> 00:39:26.382
development outside this country.

647
00:39:28.182 --> 00:39:31.542
There's also a critical point is that clinical efficacy data have yet to be

648
00:39:31.562 --> 00:39:35.522
reported on the target. So here we evaluated the potential of cadherin

649
00:39:35.562 --> 00:39:38.762
17 to act as a target for antibody drug conjugates.

650
00:39:41.142 --> 00:39:45.062
So first, we measured or estimated cadherin 17 protein

651
00:39:45.122 --> 00:39:48.422
expression in a large collection of colorectal cancer

652
00:39:49.802 --> 00:39:53.712
patient samples and saw we could detect expression in about 90% of

653
00:39:53.742 --> 00:39:57.562
samples with high intense staining in the majority of these.

654
00:39:57.592 --> 00:40:00.722
And then in normal tissues, we screened tissue microarrays for a large collection

655
00:40:00.742 --> 00:40:04.012
of normal tissues and only saw expression of the protein in normal

656
00:40:04.802 --> 00:40:06.962
small intestine and normal large intestine.

657
00:40:06.982 --> 00:40:10.692
And when I zoom in here on expression in the normal tissue, you should be able to

658
00:40:10.762 --> 00:40:14.682
see expression of cadherin 17 is localized to the lateral membranes between

659
00:40:14.722 --> 00:40:18.662
cells and absent from the basal and apical membranes, which is a

660
00:40:18.702 --> 00:40:20.522
different expression pattern that you see in cancer.

661
00:40:20.562 --> 00:40:23.802
You get this ubiquitous expression and tends throughout the cell surface.

662
00:40:24.342 --> 00:40:28.212
And these findings have been shown by a couple of other groups, and

663
00:40:28.262 --> 00:40:30.982
this provides a hypothesis by which we think we can

664
00:40:32.402 --> 00:40:35.982
use antibody-based therapies against cadherin 17, given this normal

665
00:40:36.022 --> 00:40:38.582
expression in the colon. This high

666
00:40:39.482 --> 00:40:43.282
ubiquitous expression in the cancer samples that should allow for preferential

667
00:40:43.322 --> 00:40:47.172
binding of your antibody to cadherin 17 in the cancer, and

668
00:40:47.222 --> 00:40:50.462
it's more protected in the normal colon.

669
00:40:51.022 --> 00:40:55.002
So to test this, we generated an antibody drug conjugate.

670
00:40:55.041 --> 00:40:58.362
First, we generated a monoclonal antibody selective for cadherin 17,

671
00:40:59.302 --> 00:41:02.702
generated an ADC with a VC linker, MMAE

672
00:41:02.822 --> 00:41:06.262
DAR4 payload, and then shown that this binds selectively

673
00:41:06.362 --> 00:41:09.662
to cadherin 17-positive cells, no binding to negative cells.

674
00:41:10.252 --> 00:41:13.762
In internalization studies, you can see the monoclonal antibody over 24 hours

675
00:41:13.782 --> 00:41:17.442
completely internalizes, localizes to the lysosome, as does the

676
00:41:17.522 --> 00:41:20.312
antibody drug conjugate at which we start to see cell killing.

677
00:41:21.502 --> 00:41:25.491
And then in xenograft efficacy studies, we see really nice efficacy in these

678
00:41:25.522 --> 00:41:27.682
colorectal cancer or CDX models

679
00:41:28.642 --> 00:41:31.062
that are positive for cadherin 17 shown here.

680
00:41:31.092 --> 00:41:34.491
And we also have nice activity in pancreatic cancer samples that express the

681
00:41:34.502 --> 00:41:36.842
target and then no activity in target negative.

682
00:41:38.502 --> 00:41:41.882
When we got to pharmacokinetic profiling, our

683
00:41:41.902 --> 00:41:45.702
antibody does not cross-react with

684
00:41:45.722 --> 00:41:47.242
mouse cadherin 17. So we

685
00:41:48.062 --> 00:41:51.442
do see nice cross-reactivity with monkeys cadherin 17.

686
00:41:51.512 --> 00:41:55.402
So for our pilot studies, we ran them in cynomolgus monkeys, giving a

687
00:41:55.462 --> 00:41:59.162
single dose of three mgs per kg to three male monkeys of

688
00:41:59.202 --> 00:42:02.832
three mgs per kg of our cadherin 17 ADC and

689
00:42:02.862 --> 00:42:05.462
measured exposure over 28 days.

690
00:42:06.362 --> 00:42:08.282
Our PK data show

691
00:42:09.982 --> 00:42:13.162
an acceptable PK profile for our ADC

692
00:42:14.182 --> 00:42:17.982
in, you can see, gradual degradation of the total ADC

693
00:42:18.042 --> 00:42:22.022
over time, which is consistent with minimal release of free MMAE payload.

694
00:42:22.982 --> 00:42:26.882
Overall, you could say that the half-life of our ADC is on the shorter

695
00:42:26.962 --> 00:42:30.362
side, but still well within limits that's acceptable for antibody drug conjugates.

696
00:42:31.842 --> 00:42:34.722
We then completed IND-enabling studies and

697
00:42:35.562 --> 00:42:39.202
initiated first-in-human study to evaluate safety tolerability exposure

698
00:42:39.282 --> 00:42:43.180
of our now named TORL-3600 moleculeAnd

699
00:42:43.250 --> 00:42:46.770
we got an early signal in patients that we started to see higher than

700
00:42:46.830 --> 00:42:50.030
expected, based on our pre-clinical models, clearance of our antibody drug

701
00:42:50.090 --> 00:42:54.070
conjugates. So we then moved on to see if we could identify

702
00:42:54.130 --> 00:42:58.050
why this may be happening. First mechanism, potential mechanism for this is

703
00:42:58.110 --> 00:43:01.910
clear, is that is target-mediated clearance happening to our

704
00:43:01.950 --> 00:43:05.850
antibody drug conjugate due to binding to normal expression of cadherin 17 in the

705
00:43:05.890 --> 00:43:09.480
colon and small intestine? And then second, we know that

706
00:43:09.510 --> 00:43:13.190
colorectal cancers are high expressers of P-gp pumps, so could

707
00:43:13.250 --> 00:43:14.130
changing payload

708
00:43:15.229 --> 00:43:16.260
somehow improve activity?

709
00:43:17.290 --> 00:43:21.130
So we started by looking at PK. So as I mentioned before,

710
00:43:21.250 --> 00:43:24.270
our antibody doesn't cross-react with mouse cadherin 17.

711
00:43:24.370 --> 00:43:27.740
So we purchased from BioCyteGen a humanized mouse that

712
00:43:27.850 --> 00:43:31.670
uses homologous recombination to express the human cadherin

713
00:43:31.730 --> 00:43:32.570
17 domain

714
00:43:34.210 --> 00:43:37.190
in these animals. We validated this by

715
00:43:38.190 --> 00:43:42.070
staining for using a human-specific antibody to stain for cadherin

716
00:43:42.130 --> 00:43:42.610
17

717
00:43:44.130 --> 00:43:47.890
in these

718
00:43:47.949 --> 00:43:51.490
express mice. You can see we get nice intense staining in the normal

719
00:43:51.750 --> 00:43:54.610
small and large intestine, no staining in other tissues.

720
00:43:55.290 --> 00:43:58.470
And then in wild-type animals, we see no staining with the human-specific antibody

721
00:43:58.610 --> 00:44:01.190
and then none in our efficacy CD1 nude mice model.

722
00:44:01.710 --> 00:44:05.170
When we zoom in on this staining, you can see this high intense staining in the

723
00:44:05.210 --> 00:44:08.780
lateral membranes between the cells, very similar to what with the pattern that is

724
00:44:08.810 --> 00:44:12.790
observed in human, indicating that this could be a reliable animal or model

725
00:44:13.020 --> 00:44:14.840
for estimating target-mediated clearance.

726
00:44:15.870 --> 00:44:19.390
To do this, we took wild-type mice and these humanized

727
00:44:19.450 --> 00:44:23.270
animals and gave them a single dose of 2.5 mgs of our

728
00:44:23.330 --> 00:44:26.790
cadherin 17 MMAE ADC, collected blood

729
00:44:26.830 --> 00:44:30.790
over 21 days. And in our wild-type animals, you can see

730
00:44:30.830 --> 00:44:33.110
we get nice exposure of our ADC over time.

731
00:44:33.510 --> 00:44:35.830
We get some degradation, but nice exposure.

732
00:44:35.870 --> 00:44:39.450
But in these humanized animals, we see rapid

733
00:44:39.490 --> 00:44:42.770
clearance of the cadherin 17 ADC, both total

734
00:44:42.810 --> 00:44:46.630
ADC and total antibody with complete, almost below the level of

735
00:44:46.670 --> 00:44:49.189
detection within 48 hours of dosing.

736
00:44:49.710 --> 00:44:53.430
So about fourfold higher clearance in these humanized mice, indicating that the

737
00:44:53.450 --> 00:44:57.290
presence of the human cadherin 17 in the gut of these animals is

738
00:44:57.350 --> 00:44:59.250
causing this rapid rate of clearance.

739
00:45:00.910 --> 00:45:03.230
We then went back to investigate payload.

740
00:45:03.870 --> 00:45:07.390
So I think the majority of people in the audience know that antibody drug

741
00:45:07.450 --> 00:45:11.170
conjugates payloads, by their nature, to have bystander activity, are

742
00:45:11.210 --> 00:45:14.970
hydrophobic molecules. MMAE is definitely considered to be a substrate of

743
00:45:15.010 --> 00:45:18.850
these pumps. Exetecan is also a hydrophobic molecule, but less so.

744
00:45:18.910 --> 00:45:22.670
So we wanted to see if switching our payload and our ADC, keeping the exact

745
00:45:22.710 --> 00:45:26.690
same construct, that's VC link or DAR4, but switching out just for the

746
00:45:26.710 --> 00:45:30.330
exetecan payload, and then compare activity of these

747
00:45:30.390 --> 00:45:34.370
molecules in cell line-derived xenografts expressing P-gp in colorectal.

