01:26:23.354 --> 01:26:27.033
as investigational candidates. So, so far to date, we've screened about

1464
01:26:27.313 --> 01:26:31.234
50 ADCs in the Prism platform, spanning 25 targets,

1465
01:26:31.294 --> 01:26:34.454
which are listed here on the slide, and multiple different payloads and payload

1466
01:26:34.494 --> 01:26:34.994
classes.

1467
01:26:39.474 --> 01:26:42.694
So our emerging screening results are potentially telling us

1468
01:26:43.394 --> 01:26:47.214
something we already know about ADCs, and that is that sensitivity of ADCs

1469
01:26:47.294 --> 01:26:50.294
really strongly correlates with the expression of its target antigen.

1470
01:26:50.774 --> 01:26:54.644
So here on the left, I'm showing you the box plots here of the ADCs broken

1471
01:26:54.694 --> 01:26:57.624
down by their target and colored by the different payloads that we've looked at,

1472
01:26:58.854 --> 01:27:02.134
the correlation coefficients with the target antigen.

1473
01:27:02.504 --> 01:27:06.444
And what we generally see is really strong negative correlations with our

1474
01:27:06.474 --> 01:27:10.294
target expression and sensitivity, so higher expression of our

1475
01:27:10.334 --> 01:27:13.094
target antigen that leads to more cell line sensitivity.

1476
01:27:14.594 --> 01:27:18.354
Usually, that typically comes out as gene expression, but we also see that also in

1477
01:27:18.474 --> 01:27:20.314
copy number amplification as a feature.

1478
01:27:22.974 --> 01:27:26.334
And here I just wanted to specifically highlight the clinical stage ADCs that we

1479
01:27:26.434 --> 01:27:30.174
screened, in particular, showing that these generally show very strong

1480
01:27:30.534 --> 01:27:33.754
target correlations with the antigen target

1481
01:27:34.674 --> 01:27:35.474
for these ADCs.

1482
01:27:38.334 --> 01:27:41.534
And so one thing that was really important for us to think about and consider given

1483
01:27:41.614 --> 01:27:44.734
the pooled format of the Prism screen was what would bystander

1484
01:27:44.774 --> 01:27:46.914
activity look like within this format.

1485
01:27:47.664 --> 01:27:49.884
And so essentially what we've seen here is that

1486
01:27:50.234 --> 01:27:53.954
bystander-capable ADCs and as well as non-bystander

1487
01:27:53.974 --> 01:27:56.374
capabilities both show strong target correlations.

1488
01:27:57.274 --> 01:28:01.184
And so yeah, again, in the box plots, you can see the different payloads that

1489
01:28:01.194 --> 01:28:04.774
we've screened. Again, a variety of payloads with and without bystander

1490
01:28:04.794 --> 01:28:08.134
capability. But on the right-hand side, I highlighted just two of those

1491
01:28:08.414 --> 01:28:11.694
conjugated to trastuzumab. So in the top row, you can see

1492
01:28:11.714 --> 01:28:15.624
trastuzumab conjugated to MMAE as the payload here,

1493
01:28:15.654 --> 01:28:19.534
and the bottom the same trastuzumab with the same linker conjugated to the

1494
01:28:19.574 --> 01:28:23.483
non-bystander MMAF payload. And on the far right here, I've

1495
01:28:23.514 --> 01:28:27.454
highlighted just the HER2 amplified lines showing selective activity, and we

1496
01:28:27.494 --> 01:28:30.534
see that both with bystander-capable and non-capable version.

1497
01:28:32.674 --> 01:28:36.254
And due to time constraints for the talk today, I don't have a lot of time to get

1498
01:28:36.294 --> 01:28:39.974
into the validation work we've done around looking at bystander activity in Prism,

1499
01:28:39.994 --> 01:28:43.604
but I do want to say that we've done a lot of thinking and work in this

1500
01:28:43.614 --> 01:28:47.574
regards, and it is dependent on the target expression of

1501
01:28:47.614 --> 01:28:50.954
the antigen you're looking at within our Prism cell set and as well as the

1502
01:28:50.974 --> 01:28:54.534
individual pools in the assay in combination with the particular

1503
01:28:54.594 --> 01:28:58.414
ADC payload and linker chemistry that really will

1504
01:28:58.954 --> 01:29:01.954
dictate whether or not we see bystander effect in the Prism format.

1505
01:29:04.894 --> 01:29:08.814
So as we were working to build this comprehensive screening data set, we

1506
01:29:08.854 --> 01:29:11.194
quickly ran into some challenges.

1507
01:29:12.474 --> 01:29:15.584
First and foremost being the commercial availability of ADCs.

1508
01:29:15.894 --> 01:29:19.654
So essentially we have screened and sourced everything we can get our hands

1509
01:29:19.714 --> 01:29:23.674
on commercially. So we're running out of options, they're limited

1510
01:29:23.684 --> 01:29:26.214
to come by and then also difficult for us to validate in

1511
01:29:26.334 --> 01:29:29.894
QC. Generating custom ADCs is

1512
01:29:29.934 --> 01:29:31.534
time-consuming and very expensive.

1513
01:29:32.224 --> 01:29:35.914
And for our purposes in screening, a lot of these not really realistic or

1514
01:29:35.974 --> 01:29:38.054
feasible to do on a large scale.

1515
01:29:39.594 --> 01:29:43.254
And then while unconjugated antibodies are more readily available, these

1516
01:29:43.294 --> 01:29:45.964
typically lack their own intrinsic cytotoxic activity.

1517
01:29:46.614 --> 01:29:50.424
So in a viability assay like Prism, it'll generally look mostly

1518
01:29:50.454 --> 01:29:50.973
inactive.

1519
01:29:53.774 --> 01:29:57.494
So in trying to continue to build this data set and screen more targets, we were

1520
01:29:57.554 --> 01:30:01.014
thinking of ways that we can get around some of these issues and expand our

1521
01:30:01.054 --> 01:30:04.754
screening library for more antibodies so we can look at different surface

1522
01:30:04.834 --> 01:30:08.574
targets. And also think about this as a way that in the

1523
01:30:08.674 --> 01:30:12.394
development process for ADCs, you can characterize an antibody earlier in the

1524
01:30:12.414 --> 01:30:16.214
process before having going down the workflow of developing a

1525
01:30:16.234 --> 01:30:18.674
particular antibody for a target into an ADC.

1526
01:30:22.694 --> 01:30:25.714
And so what essentially we have developed to come around this was the Prism AIR

1527
01:30:25.814 --> 01:30:29.394
assay. So AIR stands for Antibody Internalization Reporter assay.

1528
01:30:29.914 --> 01:30:33.774
And the idea of this assay is generally to

1529
01:30:33.814 --> 01:30:37.324
mimic the function of an ADC by using a universal secondary

1530
01:30:37.634 --> 01:30:38.354
drug conjugate.

1531
01:30:39.874 --> 01:30:43.334
So the assay works, essentially we have a Fab drug conjugate that is

1532
01:30:44.094 --> 01:30:46.714
conjugated to MMAF. We have a non-cleavable linker.

1533
01:30:47.454 --> 01:30:49.934
We couple this with a primary antibody.

1534
01:30:50.394 --> 01:30:53.954
Our secondary Fab works with any humanized IgG

1535
01:30:54.194 --> 01:30:58.074
antibody. This complex, again, we treat the cells, and

1536
01:30:58.134 --> 01:31:01.894
it functions much in a very similar way to an ADC, will get

1537
01:31:02.154 --> 01:31:05.944
selective killing of the cells expressing the target antigen for that

1538
01:31:05.954 --> 01:31:06.824
primary antibody.

1539
01:31:09.834 --> 01:31:13.754
So to validate Prism AIR as a readout, one of the things we did was to compare

1540
01:31:13.764 --> 01:31:15.584
the AIR format with the ADC format.

1541
01:31:15.994 --> 01:31:19.734
So here I'm showing you the example of tozotamab in which we've screened tozotamab

1542
01:31:19.874 --> 01:31:23.674
vedotin, MMAE ADC version, as well as

1543
01:31:23.714 --> 01:31:24.734
tozotamab in AIR.

1544
01:31:25.614 --> 01:31:29.294
On the left are the heat maps for viability of all the cell lines in this

1545
01:31:29.334 --> 01:31:32.434
assay. And then on the right, if you look at the

1546
01:31:32.474 --> 01:31:36.384
expression-The gene expression correlations, we see very similar

1547
01:31:37.394 --> 01:31:41.174
correlations for the AIR version as well as the ADC version for the

1548
01:31:41.214 --> 01:31:43.914
target of this antibody tissue factor or F3.

1549
01:31:45.094 --> 01:31:48.914
The scatter plot on the bottom here showing the sensitivity of this, again,

1550
01:31:49.014 --> 01:31:51.814
being nicely correlated with expression of its target.

1551
01:31:52.334 --> 01:31:53.374
And comparing the ADC

1552
01:31:54.354 --> 01:31:57.874
version with the AIR version, we see a strong concordance here, again, also

1553
01:31:57.934 --> 01:32:00.234
associated with the expression levels of the target.

1554
01:32:02.574 --> 01:32:06.463
So we're continuing to screen in the AIR platform and

1555
01:32:06.514 --> 01:32:10.494
build out this data set. So far, we've screened antibodies against 11 different

1556
01:32:10.503 --> 01:32:14.494
targets listed here in both the antibody, the AIR

1557
01:32:14.574 --> 01:32:18.334
formats, and the ADC format. On the right-hand side, I'm showing you a

1558
01:32:18.394 --> 01:32:21.774
scatter plot of the target correlations for the AIR versus the ADC

1559
01:32:21.834 --> 01:32:25.714
formats. So we've looked at a variety of different ADCs

1560
01:32:26.014 --> 01:32:27.774
with payloads for the same targets here.

1561
01:32:28.454 --> 01:32:31.994
The points colored by the payload of the ADC version.

1562
01:32:32.174 --> 01:32:35.854
And largely you see good concordance with the target correlations across various

1563
01:32:36.474 --> 01:32:37.854
different antibodies and targets.

1564
01:32:38.354 --> 01:32:39.253
Where we do see

1565
01:32:40.074 --> 01:32:44.014
outliers or differential activity, it tends to be payload-specific

1566
01:32:44.074 --> 01:32:48.054
differences. So here, highlighting ceticizumab conjugated

1567
01:32:48.094 --> 01:32:51.224
to the SN 38 has a very differential profile compared to

1568
01:32:51.294 --> 01:32:54.374
ceticizumab in the AIR format with the MMAF payload.

1569
01:32:58.134 --> 01:33:01.714
And in this final slide, I wanted to highlight ways that we think

1570
01:33:01.854 --> 01:33:05.514
using PRISM AIR can really help us better understand and characterize

1571
01:33:06.534 --> 01:33:08.134
ADCs and antibody targets.

1572
01:33:09.194 --> 01:33:12.874
I'm using the example of a panel of four Trop-2 targeting

1573
01:33:12.914 --> 01:33:15.874
agents that we've screened in the AIR in ADC format.

1574
01:33:16.194 --> 01:33:19.894
So we've screened datopotamab and ceticizumab, again, both targeting

1575
01:33:19.934 --> 01:33:23.674
Trop-2 or taxane-2, in AIR and ADCs.

1576
01:33:23.894 --> 01:33:27.844
If we start maybe by looking at the ceticizumab here, what we see is

1577
01:33:27.894 --> 01:33:31.654
unlike all of the others, where we get very strong correlations with the target,

1578
01:33:32.034 --> 01:33:35.954
ceticizumab does not significantly correlate with its target antigen.

1579
01:33:36.654 --> 01:33:40.634
And based on what we know about the linker chemistry of ceticizumab, this

1580
01:33:40.714 --> 01:33:44.224
is unsurprising, being unstable and releasing free payload.

1581
01:33:44.614 --> 01:33:48.494
And indeed, if we look at ceticizumab gavitan compared to just the free payload

1582
01:33:48.574 --> 01:33:50.584
alone, these are strongly correlated.

1583
01:33:50.614 --> 01:33:51.374
And we also get

1584
01:33:52.234 --> 01:33:56.194
biomarkers that are associated with sensitivity to the payload, like

1585
01:33:56.234 --> 01:33:58.274
SLAFN11 coming up as biomarkers.

1586
01:34:01.174 --> 01:34:04.374
And then if we look at the AIR for the datopotamab

1587
01:34:04.834 --> 01:34:05.674
versus the

1588
01:34:06.834 --> 01:34:10.774
datopotamab AIR data versus the datopotamab ADC data, one of the things we

1589
01:34:10.794 --> 01:34:14.754
were also interested in looking for was looking for differential drivers of linker

1590
01:34:14.834 --> 01:34:16.254
payload-specific sensitivity.

1591
01:34:17.054 --> 01:34:20.594
So here is a scatter plot, again, plotting datopotamab

1592
01:34:20.614 --> 01:34:24.394
deruxtecan DXd payload versus datopotamab AIR with the

1593
01:34:24.494 --> 01:34:28.184
MMAF payload. And we were doing a differential expression

1594
01:34:28.214 --> 01:34:31.974
analysis to look for drivers of sensitivity, and we can see a bunch of

1595
01:34:32.014 --> 01:34:35.714
things pop out here. Expression of these

1596
01:34:35.734 --> 01:34:38.674
driving sensitivity to one payload over the other.

1597
01:34:38.794 --> 01:34:42.654
I wanted to highlight the SLC46A3 in particular.

1598
01:34:42.844 --> 01:34:46.074
This is a lysosomal transporter that has been previously implicated as being

1599
01:34:46.114 --> 01:34:49.354
