1603
01:35:00.254 --> 01:35:04.074
However, our data does show that the low expression of this can confer resistance

1604
01:35:04.354 --> 01:35:07.234
to particular non-cleavable linkers with the MMF payload.

1605
01:35:07.684 --> 01:35:10.374
This is something we've seen consistently across everything we've screened in our

1606
01:35:10.444 --> 01:35:13.923
AIR format that we don't see with different ADCs or

1607
01:35:14.494 --> 01:35:15.454
different linker payloads.

1608
01:35:18.074 --> 01:35:20.024
So to conclude, we think PRISM screening

1609
01:35:21.114 --> 01:35:23.804
can shed light on numerous factors that impact ADC activity.

1610
01:35:24.394 --> 01:35:27.994
Screening can be used to uncover novel targets, profile

1611
01:35:28.074 --> 01:35:31.274
selectivity of candidate antibodies, and identify potentially new patient

1612
01:35:31.314 --> 01:35:35.234
populations for therapeutics. We're actively using PRISM AIR to continue

1613
01:35:35.254 --> 01:35:38.394
screening antibodies and building our reference data set, which will be made

1614
01:35:38.514 --> 01:35:39.714
publicly available in the future.

1615
01:35:40.744 --> 01:35:44.324
And we think this will enable us, as well as collaborators who are interested in

1616
01:35:44.434 --> 01:35:48.264
screening with us, to functionally validate new surface targets for

1617
01:35:48.294 --> 01:35:49.044
ADC development.

